title: Google\Cloud\Domains\V1beta1\TransferParameters
name: TransferParameters
description:
Parameters required to transfer a domain from another registrar.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.domains.v1beta1.TransferParameters

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.domain_name
params.description: The domain name. Unicode domain names are expressed in Punycode format.

params.name: data.current_registrar
params.description: The registrar that currently manages the domain.

params.name: data.name_servers
params.description: The name servers that currently store the configuration of the domain.

params.name: data.transfer_lock_state
params.description: Indicates whether the domain is protected by a transfer lock. For a transfer to succeed, this must show UNLOCKED. To unlock a domain, go to its current registrar.

params.name: data.supported_privacy
params.description: Contact privacy options that the domain supports.

params.name: data.yearly_price
params.description: Price to transfer or renew the domain for one year.
